WEBVTT

00:08.525 --> 00:10.117
Will the defendant please rise?

00:15.532 --> 00:17.967
In the matter of
The People vs. Stanley Coe...

00:17.967 --> 00:19.169
having found the defendant...

00:19.169 --> 00:22.572
guilty of the murder
of Nicholas Janus...

00:22.572 --> 00:23.840
the jury has recommended...

00:23.840 --> 00:25.675
that you not receive
the death penalty.

00:25.675 --> 00:28.511
Given the mitigating factors
in your case...

00:28.511 --> 00:29.779
it is the order of this court...

00:29.779 --> 00:32.148
that you serve
no less than 15 years...

00:32.148 --> 00:34.384
and no more
than the term of your life.

00:34.384 --> 00:36.019
Case closed.
Jury is dismissed.

00:36.019 --> 00:39.923
No! That son of a bitch
killed my husband.

00:39.923 --> 00:41.891
You don't deserve to live.

00:41.891 --> 00:44.086
This isn't justice.
It's a joke.

00:45.528 --> 00:47.897
Born into a life
of wealth and privilege...

00:47.897 --> 00:51.301
Laurel Janus has always gotten
exactly what she wants.

00:51.301 --> 00:53.236
But with the murder
of her husband...

00:53.236 --> 00:56.039
Laurel's life of luxury
has been shattered.

00:56.039 --> 01:00.276
Now, all she wants
is to see justice done...

01:00.276 --> 01:04.247
a justice
that can only be found...

01:04.247 --> 01:06.306
in The Twilight Zone.

01:07.717 --> 01:08.918
How could you blow it
like this?

01:08.918 --> 01:10.453
What kind of
a D.A. are you, Lew?

01:10.453 --> 01:11.654
I know it's not
what you were hoping for...

01:11.654 --> 01:13.790
but I did the best I could
with the evidence I had.

01:13.790 --> 01:15.391
Great. So Nick
had his brains bashed in...

01:15.391 --> 01:17.393
and Coe gets free meals,
pay-per-view.

01:17.393 --> 01:19.195
Who knows? Maybe he'll
even write his memoirs.

01:19.195 --> 01:21.531
Laurel, it's over. You won.

01:21.531 --> 01:23.533
You've got my card, Laurel.

01:23.533 --> 01:24.898
If you need anything,
just call me. OK?

01:27.137 --> 01:29.739
My husband's things.
When can I have them back?

01:29.739 --> 01:30.940
Well, that's hard to say.

01:30.940 --> 01:32.375
It's not exactly
proper procedure.

01:32.375 --> 01:33.777
I'm not asking for the evidence.

01:33.777 --> 01:35.578
I just want the things
he wore that night.

01:35.578 --> 01:36.772
Please, Lew.

01:37.781 --> 01:38.975
OK.

01:41.751 --> 01:42.986
Let me drive you home.

01:42.986 --> 01:45.355
Come on. You know me.
I'm a pillar of strength.

01:45.355 --> 01:47.824
Uh-huh. We can get your car
in the morning.

01:47.824 --> 01:49.159
I'm fine, Becca. Really.

01:49.159 --> 01:50.460
Are you sure?

01:50.460 --> 01:53.463
Hey, I've been clean for
sixteen weeks and three days.

01:53.463 --> 01:54.864
No pills, no booze.

01:54.864 --> 01:56.833
God knows I've been tempted.

01:56.833 --> 01:58.468
OK, well, you call me
the minute you get home.

01:58.468 --> 02:00.603
Yes, Mother.

02:00.603 --> 02:02.906
Becca.

02:02.906 --> 02:04.140
Thanks for being there.

02:04.140 --> 02:06.199
What are mothers for!

